      <h3>Irish Moss vs. Jamaican Sea Moss: What You Need to Know</h3>

      <p>Not all sea moss is created equal. True Irish moss (<em>Chondrus crispus</em>) grows along the rocky Atlantic coasts of Ireland, Iceland, and parts of North America. It has a flat, fan-shaped structure and comes in dark purple, red, or golden yellow varieties. Jamaican sea moss, often marketed as "purple sea moss" or "gold sea moss," is typically <em>Gracilaria</em>, a different genus of red algae that grows in warmer tropical waters.</p>

      <div class="tip-box"><div class="tip-box-ico">i</div><p><strong><em>Chondrus crispus</em> generally has higher concentrations</strong> of iodine, potassium, and carrageenan compared to <em>Gracilaria</em>. Wildcrafted varieties absorb minerals directly from nutrient-rich ocean water, while pool-grown varieties may produce a less diverse mineral profile. Premium brands like Maju Superfoods and Elm &amp; Rye specifically source wildcrafted <em>Chondrus crispus</em>.</p></div>

