      <!-- ====== FAQ ====== -->
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Sea Moss Gummies</h2>

      <details class="fq">
        <summary>What does sea moss do for your body?</summary>
        <p>Sea moss (<em>Chondrus crispus</em>) contains 92 of the 102 minerals the human body needs, including iodine, potassium, calcium, magnesium, iron, and zinc. It supports thyroid function through its natural iodine content, promotes healthy digestion as a prebiotic fiber source, and provides antioxidant compounds that may reduce inflammation. A 2021 study published in <em>Marine Drugs</em> identified bioactive compounds in sea moss with anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties. Most users report improvements in energy, digestion, and skin clarity within 2-4 weeks of consistent use.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="fq">
        <summary>Are sea moss gummies tested for heavy metals?</summary>
        <p>Reputable brands conduct third-party testing for heavy metals including lead, arsenic, mercury, and cadmium. Because sea moss is a marine organism, it can accumulate heavy metals from ocean water, making independent testing essential. In our review, 6 of 8 recommended products provide verified third-party testing with a Certificate of Analysis (COA) available. We strongly recommend choosing products with documented third-party testing, especially given the rapid growth of the sea moss supplement market and the influx of untested products.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="fq">
        <summary>Can sea moss gummies cause iodine overdose?</summary>
        <p>Sea moss is naturally high in iodine, and excessive iodine intake can disrupt thyroid function, causing either hyperthyroidism or hypothyroidism. The recommended daily allowance of iodine for adults is 150 mcg, with an upper tolerable limit of 1,100 mcg. Most sea moss gummies provide between 50-150 mcg of iodine per serving, which falls within safe limits for healthy adults. However, if you take thyroid medication, have Hashimoto's thyroiditis or Graves' disease, or are already taking an iodine supplement, consult your doctor before adding sea moss to your routine.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="fq">
        <summary>How long does it take to see results from sea moss gummies?</summary>
        <p>Most users report noticing initial benefits within 2-4 weeks of consistent daily use. Digestive improvements, such as reduced bloating and more regular bowel movements, tend to appear first, followed by improved energy levels. Skin and hair benefits typically take 6-8 weeks to become noticeable. The timeline depends on your baseline mineral status, overall diet quality, the quality of the sea moss product, and individual biological factors. For best results, take sea moss gummies at the same time each day, ideally with a meal to improve mineral absorption.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="fq">
        <summary>What is the Dr. Sebi trinity formula?</summary>
        <p>The "Dr. Sebi trinity" is the combination of sea moss, bladderwrack, and burdock root, popularized by the late Honduran herbalist Dr. Sebi (Alfredo Darrington Bowman). This combination is believed to provide comprehensive mineral and nutritional support: sea moss delivers 92 minerals, bladderwrack (<em>Fucus vesiculosus</em>) adds fucoxanthin and additional iodine for thyroid support, and burdock root (<em>Arctium lappa</em>) provides prebiotic inulin for gut health and supports detoxification. Five of our eight recommended products include all three ingredients in their formulas.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="fq">
        <summary>Is wildcrafted sea moss better than farm-grown?</summary>
        <p>Wildcrafted sea moss is harvested from natural ocean environments where it absorbs minerals directly from seawater, potentially producing a richer and more diverse mineral profile. Farm-grown (also called "pool-grown") sea moss is cultivated in controlled environments, often using ropes or tanks, which may result in a less complex nutrient composition. Independent testing has generally shown higher mineral concentrations in wildcrafted varieties. However, wildcrafted sea moss costs more, and overharvesting raises sustainability concerns. Farm-grown sea moss is more affordable and can still provide meaningful nutritional benefits, making it a viable option for budget-conscious buyers.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="fq">
        <summary>Can you take sea moss gummies while pregnant?</summary>
        <p>Sea moss contains nutrients important during pregnancy, including folate, iron, and iodine. However, you should always consult your OB-GYN or midwife before starting any supplement during pregnancy or breastfeeding. The primary concern is iodine content, as excessive iodine can affect fetal thyroid development. Since most prenatal vitamins already contain iodine (typically 150-220 mcg), adding sea moss could push your total iodine intake above the recommended 220 mcg for pregnant women. Additionally, some sea moss products contain heavy metals that could be harmful during pregnancy, so third-party testing is especially critical for expectant mothers.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="fq">
        <summary>Are sea moss gummies FDA approved?</summary>
        <p>No. Like all dietary supplements sold in the United States, sea moss gummies are not FDA approved. Under the Dietary Supplement Health and Education Act (DSHEA) of 1994, the FDA does not evaluate dietary supplements for safety and efficacy before they reach the market. Manufacturers are responsible for ensuring their products are safe and that label claims are truthful, and they must follow current Good Manufacturing Practices (cGMP). To protect yourself, choose brands that use FDA-registered facilities, provide third-party testing through organizations like NSF International or USP, and avoid products making specific disease treatment claims, which are illegal for dietary supplements.</p>
      </details>

